==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stoichiology
<hw>Stoi`chi*ol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ a
first element + <ets>-logy</ets>.]</ety> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>stoechiology</asp>.]</altsp> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That part of the
science of physiology which treats of the elements, or principles,
composing animal tissues.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Logic)</fld> <def>The doctrine of the elementary
requisites of mere thought.</def> <rj><au>Sir W. Hamilton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The statement or discussion of the first principles
of any science or art.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stoichiometrical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Stoichiometric</ent>⟦br⟧
